  <div id="content">
  <p>I love to step away from the computer to play the tabletop roleplaying game,
     <a href="http://paizo.com/pathfinder">Pathfinder</a>.</p>
  <h2>Bay Area Pathfinder Society</h2>
  <p>I'm a <a href="http://paizo.com/people/Yasumoto">Venture Lieutenant for San Francisco</a>,
     which means I help organize events and conventions, in addition to
     <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BayAreaPathfinderSociety">running our Facebook page</a>.
     If you're in the San Francisco Bay Area, there are a lot of great games hosted by the
     <a href="https://bayareapathfinder.com">Bay Area Pathfinder Society</a>! In particular,
     <a href="https://warhorn.net/events/endgame">Endgame in Oakland</a> hosts events on Monday
     evenings, and <a href="https://warhorn.net/events/gamescape-sf-pfs">Gamescape in San Francisco</a>
     hosts a Saturday game day each month.</p>
  <h2>Publications</h2>
  <p>Zenith Games recently published
     <a href="http://zenithgames.blogspot.com/2016/10/the-colossal-creatures-bestiary.html">The Colossal Creatures Bestiary</a>
     which contains a massive Raccoon-like creature I designed called a <i>Procyon</i>! It was a great
     experience to work with that group, and it's available
     <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9p9l/discuss?The-Colossal-Creatures-Bestiary">on the Paizo webstore</a>
     if you'd like to take a look!</p>
  <p>The fine folks behind <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9e73?Wayfinder-13">Wayfinder #13</a>
     also published my description of two characters based in the city of Caliphas! Spanning two
     pages and 1500 words, you can read about both <a href="images/wayfinder_13_almira.jpg">Captain Almira Perine</a>
     and <a href="images/wayfinder_13_liald.jpg">Captain Liald Gaspair</a>! The character art is by the
     <a href="http://bobgreyvenstein.deviantart.com">amazing Bob Greyvenstein</a>.
  </p>
